Wash and dry all produce. Bring a medium #pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Peel and mince the @ginger{1%thumb}. Remove and discard the @kale{4%oz} stems and ribs, then roughly chop the leaves. Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Finely mince the @Thai chili{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large #pot{} over medium heat. Add the sliced red onion to the pot and cook, stirring for ~{2%minutes}, until slightly softened. Add the garlic, ginger, and as much Thai chili as you like (start with a little and go up from there!). Cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant.

Add the @ground pork{10%oz} to the same pot, breaking up the meat into pieces, and cook for ~{5-6%minutes}, until browned. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @water{4%cups} and the @pho stock concentrate{2} to the pot with the pork. Stir to combine, then add the kale and @soy sauce{6%tsp}. Bring to a simmer for ~{5%minutes}, until the kale is just tender.

Add the @ramen noodles{9%oz} to the pot of salted water and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}, or until al dente. Drain and add to the soup.

Serve divided between bowls and enjoy!

> Thick ramen noodles are perfect for slurping, which is exactly what you'll be doing with this unctuous pork soup. Thai chilies pack some serious heat - be sure to add with caution!